<!-- ============ ARTICLE ============ -->
<section class="sec" style="padding-top:40px">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="post-wrap post-body reveal">
<p>Explainer videos maximize customer conversion by building understanding and trust at the same time — the two factors that determine whether a prospect buys. According to Wyzowl's 2024 State of Video Marketing report, 96% of people have watched an <a href={p("services/how-to-video")}>explainer video</a> to learn about a product, and 89% say it convinced them to make a purchase.</p><h2>The Role of Explainer Videos in Customer Conversion</h2><p>When it comes to getting customers to buy, two things matter most: understanding and trust. If someone doesn't grasp what a product does, they won't buy it; if they don't trust the brand, they'll hesitate even more. Explainer videos tackle both challenges by presenting information in an engaging way that's easy to understand, and a professional-looking video builds trust with viewers.</p><h2>Simplifying the Customer Journey</h2><p>Every customer goes through a journey that starts with awareness, moves to consideration, and ends with a decision. Explainer videos make this journey smoother by breaking complicated ideas into simple, bite-sized pieces, addressing pain points and answering questions before they even arise.</p><h2>Building an Emotional Connection Through Storytelling</h2><p>Emotions play a huge role in buying decisions. Explainer videos mix information with storytelling to create an emotional bond with viewers rather than just listing features — showing, for example, how a <a href={p("services/product-video")}>product</a> saves time or solves a common problem. Research from Google shows that 40% of YouTube users look for videos to learn more about products they're considering, and relatable stories boost the chances of conversion.</p><h2>Leveraging Visuals for Clarity and Engagement</h2><p>Visuals are essential for explaining complex products or services. Explainer videos use animations, graphics, and visual metaphors to make messages clearer and more memorable — showing a product in action rather than just describing it. Studies show people remember 80% of what they see, compared to only 20% of what they read, which is why explainer videos deliver information that sticks.</p><h2>Optimizing Explainer Videos for Conversion</h2><ul><li><strong>Length:</strong> aim for 60 to 90 seconds to keep viewers' attention.</li><li><strong>Call to action:</strong> include a clear CTA that tells viewers what to do next, like signing up or making a purchase.</li><li><strong>Placement:</strong> put videos on landing pages or in emails to reach the right audience at the right time.</li><li><strong>Mobile compatibility:</strong> make sure videos look great on phones, where most viewing happens.</li></ul><p>According to Unbounce, including a video on a landing page can increase conversions by up to 80%, since explainer videos provide instant value by answering questions and addressing concerns quickly.</p><h2>Measuring the Impact of Explainer Videos</h2><p>Key metrics to track include view count, engagement rate (how long viewers watch), click-through rate, and conversion rate. Monitoring these helps improve video content and strategy over time — the same discipline covered in our post on <a href={p("blog/unlocking-business-growth-the-power-of-explainer-videos-in-generating-quality-leads")}>how explainer videos generate quality leads</a>.</p><h2>Partner with Viven to Increase Conversions</h2><p>At Viven, we specialize in creating explainer videos that drive customer conversions, tailored to a brand's needs for clarity, engagement, and measurable results — including for B2B companies, as shown in <a href={p("blog/how-b2b-companies-simplify-complex-products-with-explainer-videos")}>how B2B companies simplify complex products with explainer videos</a>.</p><p><a href={p("contact")}>Ready to take your conversion strategy to the next level? Let's get started today.</a></p>
    </div>
    <p class="post-service-note"><a href={p("services/how-to-video")}>Want to see how this works in practice? Explore our how-to & tutorial production.</a></p>
